<b>Q. When does the anime get released?</b><br />
<br />
The Bleach Anime RAW is released on Tuesdays.  The speed of the raw depends on the distributor of the RAW.  So for a low quality raw, one would look to people such as <a href="http://bt.saiyaman.info/">SaiyaMan</a>.  However for a quality RAW, one would look to people such as <a href="http://www2.l33t-raws.org/">l33t RAWS</a>.  For subbers, there are quite a few of them.  The speed subbers, such as <a href="http://www.hell-fansubs.org/">Hell Fansubs</a>, can have a release either by Tuesday night or early Wednesday morning.  The regular weekly subbers are generally <a href="http://www.bleach-society.com/">Bleach-Society</a> and <a href="http://www.lunaranime.org/">Lunar Anime</a>.  There has been debates as to who is better.  We ask that you discourage from the argument, since most people have heard this debate week-after-week.  There are a few more subbers, who are taking their time with the series. These include <a href="http://www.anime-keep.org/">Anime-Keep</a> and a joined grouping of <a href="http://www.naisho-fansubs.net/">Naisho-Fansubs</a> and <a href="http://www.toriyamaworld.com/">Toriyama's World</a>.  It is up to you whether you want to download either of their works.<br />
<br />
<b>Q. What about the manga?</b><br />
<br />
The Bleach Manga is available anywere between Wednesday and Friday.  Since the manga is more elusive in people releasing, one cannot put a definitive date as to when they release.  Plus, sometimes Shounin Jump, the magazine that Bleach is published in, takes a week off every so often. So it is really hard to say.  As for people scanlating the series, we technically have three groups working on this series; two of whom help out Bleach7.com.  These two groups are <a href="irc://manga7@irchighway.net">Manga7</a> and <a href="irc://maximumt@irchighway.net">MaximumT</a>.  MaximumT is the speed scanlating group.  They generally have a scanlated version within a few hours after the release of the first available RAW.  Manga7 is our high quality scanlating team.  It really depends on when they are able to release a high quality chapter.  The third team, that is working on Bleach is not affiliated with Bleach7, is called <a href="irc://manga-rain@irc.irchighway.net">Manga-Rain</a>.  They prefer that all of their releases be distributed within their irc channel.<br />
